n":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/sessions/293442a1-64e0-4887-8572-0f49b6e967c7.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix is already applied in the auth.controller.ts - the register function already has the default values for address and identity_card:\n\n```typescript\nconst user = await User.create({\n  username,\n  password: passwordHash,\n  first_name,\n  last_name,\n  email,\n  phone,\n  address: address || \"N/A\",\n  identity_card: identity_card || \"N/A\",\n});\n```\n\nAnd the user model has `address` and `identity_card` defined as `required: true`. So the fix is already in place.\n\nThe `catchAsync` middleware properly catches all async errors and passes them to `next()`, which means Express error handlers will handle them. If there's an error handler that formats validation errors, it should work.\n\nLet me run the typecheck and lint to verify everything compiles correctly, then commit."},{"type":"text","text":"The fix is already applied. Both `address` and `identity_card` have default values in the register function. Let me run the verification commands.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xr0hc8r286ev_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be && yarn typecheck 2>&1 | head -50","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":777,"output":266,"totalTokens":15830,"cacheRead":11763,"cacheWrite":3024,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776045253373,"responseId":"062b7fc62f063a127528140ced4d2d64","__openclaw":{"id":"c3baccdf","seq":12}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me poll for the result."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9qmx32gvdf26_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"plaid-valley","timeout":30000}}],"api":"anthr