datedAt":1775990629434,"sessionId":"731cf84b-b802-4c4a-90b9-2fb6c1177f22","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":20343,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775990537840,"endedAt":1775990629120,"runtimeMs":91280,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","lastTo":"telegram:-5168104492","lastAccountId":"prompt-optimizer_bot","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/731cf84b-b802-4c4a-90b9-2fb6c1177f22.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/prompt_optimizer tối ưu phần prompt sau: master thực hiện triển khai yêu cầu đánh giá, báo cáo cho tôi chi tiết về hệ thống qlhv này xem là có match database với master chưa, có phần logic nào chưa khớp hay có những vấn đề gì"}],"timestamp":1775990537839,"__openclaw":{"id":"32772091","seq":4},"senderLabel":"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to optimize a prompt. Let me follow the SKILL.md pipeline carefully.\n\n**Phase 0: Project Detection**\nI need to check if `GEMINI.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md` exist. I know `AGENTS.md` exists (it's in my project context). Let me check the workspace structure to detect the tech stack and available skills.\n\n**Phase 1: Intent Detection**\nThe prompt is about \"đánh giá, báo cáo\" (evaluate, report) about the \"qlhv\" system - checking if it matches the database with master, checking logic alignment, and identifying issues. This falls under **Review** and **Research** categories.\n\n\n**Phase 2: Scope Assessment**\nThe request is asking for a comprehensive system review with multiple dimensions - database alignment, logic consistency, and issue identification - which puts this at MEDIUM-HIGH scope.\n\n**Phase 3: Agent Ecosystem**\nFor this kind of cross-domain evaluation and reporting, I need to identify which components from the ecosystem can help assess the system's current state against the master.\n\n**Phase 4: Missing Context Detection**\nThe prompt has several gaps: the technology stack isn't specified, the exact system architecture isn't clear, there's no defined scope for what should be reviewed, and the desired output format isn't specified.\n\n**Phase 5: Workflow & Model**\nThis review work needs the orchestrator's guidance to coordinate the evaluation process.\n\nNow I'm drafting an optimized prompt based on these findings."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_meb0ixkx9ov3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_meb0ixkx9ov3_2","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"qlhv hệ thống database master"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":4464,"output":373,"totalTokens":20150,"cacheRead":10789,"cacheWrite":4524,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775990537849,"responseId":"062aaa0b81d4ef2177ee0d81ff5f5b25","__openclaw":{"id":"1fa36a34","seq":5}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the full ecosystem. No `qlhv` found in memory. Let me now analyze the prompt and produce the optimization output.\n\nLet me now run the full Phase 0-5 analysis and produce the output.\n\n**Project Detection:**\n- AGENTS.md exists (confirmed via context)\n- No package.json detected (empty dir listing - this is a skills workspace, not a code project)\n- Tech stack: **unknown** — no code files detected in current workspace\n\n**Intent Detection:**\n- Keywords: \"đánh giá\", \"báo cáo\", \"match database\", \"logic chưa khớp\", \"vấn đề\"\n- Category: **Review** + **Research** — a system audit/evaluation task\n"},{"type":"text","text":"## ⚙️ Prompt Diagnosis\n\n### Prompt gốc:\n> *\"master thực hiện triển khai yêu cầu đánh giá, báo cáo cho tôi chi tiết về hệ thống qlhv này xem là có match database với master chưa, có phần logic nào chưa khớp hay có những vấn đề gì\"*\n\n---\n\n### Strengths\n- ✅ Mục tiêu rõ: đánh giá hệ thống `qlhv` — so khớp DB + logic\n- ✅ Có yêu cầu báo cáo chi tiết\n\n### Issues\n\n| Issue | Impact | Suggested Fix |\n|-------|--------|---------------|\n| Không chỉ rõ **hệ thống qlhv** nằm ở đâu (repo, đường dẫn, project) | Agent không tìm được codebase → trả lời sai hoặc thừa | Cung cấp repo path hoặc workspace chứa hệ thống qlhv |\n| Không chỉ rõ **\"master\"** là ai — là agent `@master-orchestrator`, một repo cụ thể, hay branch/commit? | Routing nhầm → sai agent | Chỉ rõ agent phụ trách hoặc source of truth |\n| Không có **acceptance criteria** — khi nào thì báo cáo đủ? | Kết quả mở, không biết dừng ở đâu | Thêm tiêu chí đánh giá cụ thể |\n| Không phân biệt **database nào vs database nào** — so khớp cái gì? | Không rõ scope so sánh | Liệt kê schema cần so sánh (source DB vs target DB) |\n| Không chỉ rõ **output format** — báo cáo dạng bảng, markdown, issue list? | Không đồng nhất | Chỉ rõ format: markdown / Confluence / file |\n| Không chỉ rõ **phạm vi logic** — là tầng nào (API, service, repository)? | Kiểm tra lan man hoặc thiếu | Giới hạn: chỉ logic nghiệp vụ + database layer |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Components\n\n| Type | Component | Purpose |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| Orchestrator | `@master-orchestrator` | Điều phối cross-domain review, giao việc cho các agent chuyên biệt |\n| Skill | `@database-schema-designer` | So khớp schema, phát hiện missing/extra fields, FK constraints |\n| Skill | `@senior-backend` | Review logic nghiệp vụ, API contracts, service layer |\n| Skill | `@coding-standards` | Kiểm tra naming, patterns, DRY/KISS compliance |\n| Skill | `@senior-security` | Phát hiện vấn đề bảo mật trong DB access |\n\n---\n\n## Optimized Prompt — Full Version\n\n```\n## Task: Đánh giá & Báo cáo Hệ thống QLHV — So khớp Database & Logic\n\n### 1. Ngữ cảnh\n- Hệ thống: QLHV (Quản lý Học viên)\n- Vị trí codebase: <CHỈ_RỜI_ĐƯỜNG_DẪN_REPO_QLHV>  ← THAY BẰNG PATH THỰC TẾ\n- Database nguồn (source): <TÊN_DB_QLHV>  ← VD: MongoDB collection \"students\", \"courses\"\n- Database master (target): <TÊN_DB_MASTER>  ← VD: MongoDB collection \"students\", \"courses\"\n- Tech stack phát hiện: <AUTO_DETECT_HOẶC_CHỈ_RỖ>\n\n### 2. Mục tiêu\nSo khớp hệ thống QLHV với master, phát hiện:\n  a) **Database mismatch** — thiếu field, thừa field, sai kiểu dữ liệu, FK orphan\n  b) **Logic misalignment** — business rules không đồng nhất giữa service layer vs DB\n  c) **Vấn đề tiềm ẩn** — security holes, missing validations, edge cases chưa xử lý\n\n### 3. Workflow thực hiện\n\n**Bước 1 — @database-schema-designer**\n  → Dump schema của cả 2 database (source QLHV + master)\n  → So sánh field-by-field, type, constraints, indexes\n  → Output: Bảng diff schema (field mới / thiếu / sai type)\n\n**Bước 2 — @senior-backend**\n  → Review logic nghiệp vụ trong service layer của QLHV\n  → Kiểm tra API endpoints: request/response contract có match DB schema không\n  → Output: Danh sách logic chưa khớp hoặc thiếu validation\n\n**Bước 3 — @senior-security**\n  → Kiểm tra truy vấn DB: có SQL/NoSQL injection không?\n  → Kiểm tra quyền truy cập, auth enforcement\n  → Output: Danh sách rủi ro bảo mật (nếu có)\n\n**Bước 4 — @master-orchestrator**\n  → Tổng hợp kết quả từ Bước 1–3\n  → Phân loại: 🔴 Critical / 🟡 Warning / 🟢 OK\n\n### 4. Output format (bắt buộc)\n\n#### 4.1 Database Diff Table\n| Schema | Collection/Table | Field | Type (QLHV) | Type (Master) | Status |\n|--------|-----------------|-------|-------------|---------------|--------|\n\n#### 4.2 Logic Issues List\n| # | Module | Issue | Severity | Recommendation |\n|---|--------|-------|----------|----------------|\n\n#### 4.3 Security Issues List\n| # | Endpoint/Function | Issue | CVSS-like | Fix |\n\n#### 4.4 Summary\n- Tổng số mismatch: X\n- Tổng số logic issue: Y\n- Tổng số security issue: Z\n- ✅ Có thể proceed hay ❌ Cần fix trước\n\n### 5. Ràng buộc\n- Không sửa code — chỉ đánh giá và báo cáo\n- Không modify database production\n- Nếu repo không tìm thấy → báo lỗi ngay và hỏi lại path\n\n### 6. Deliverable\n- Báo cáo hoàn chỉnh dạng Markdown\n- Đăng lên Confluence page nếu có QLHV workspace\n\n```\n\n---\n\n## Optimized Prompt — Quick Version\n\n| Intent | Quick Pattern |\n|--------|--------------|\n| Review | `@master-orchestrator — đánh giá hệ thống QLHV. So khớp DB + logic vs master. Báo cáo table format: diff schema / logic issues / security. Không sửa, chỉ report.` |\n\n---\n\n## Enhancement Rationale\n\n| Enhancement | Reason |\n|-------------|--------|\n| Chỉ rõ repo path + collection/table | Agent biết đâu là source để review — tránh hallucinate |\n| Phân tách Bước 1–3 theo skill chuyên biệt | Đảm bảo mỗi góc nhìn được expert xử lý (DB ≠ logic ≠ security) |\n| Output table format bắt buộc | Lead nhận được artifact đồng nhất, không phải text tự do |\n| Phân loại severity (Critical/Warning/OK) | Lead có thể prioritize action ngay |\n| Không sửa, chỉ report | Đảm bảo agent không tự ý thay đổi production — đúng scope review |\n\n---\n\n> ⚠️ **Missing Info cần bạn cung cấp thêm:**\n> 1. **Repo/workspace chứa hệ thống QLHV** nằm ở đâu?\n> 2. **Tên database + collection/table** cần so khớp là gì?\n> 3. **Branch/commit master** nào là source of truth?\n> 4. **Output đích** — gửi ở đâu (Telegram/Confluence/file)?\n> 5. **Confluence space** có sẵn cho QLHV không?\n\nCung cấp thêm thông tin trên → prompt sẵn sàng paste vào agent để thực thi ngay."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":298,"output":2220,"totalTokens":22563,"cacheRead":15219,"cacheWrite":4826,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775990590009,"responseId":"062aaa3ea767173804f105306e5622f6","__openclaw":{"id":"7a8098b4","seq":8}}]},{"key":"agent:prompt-optimizer:subagent:0eb3c914-87cc-4bdd-9ee9-20aa3e6473e1","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492","displayName":"telegram:g-ahv-qlhv-ecosystem","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775990263239,"sessionId":"f3fea8c0-f2eb-474e-9c08-b41766f765ad","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775990261918,"endedAt":1775990286627,"runtimeMs":24709,"thinkingLevel":"medium","lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/f3fea8c0-f2eb-474e-9c08-b41766f765ad.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:prompt-optimizer:telegram:slash:6053576134","kind":"group","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"prompt-optimizer_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-ahv-qlhv-ecosystem","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775990178347,"sessionId":"0d74c438-5460-4bbd-824a-3bdd04655170","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/prompt-optimizer/sessions/0d74c438-5460-4bbd-824a-3bdd04655170.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:security-reviewer:subagent:6739034d-567f-4c51-8557-f54f81ff565a","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:security","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982753509,"sessionId":"e0e07a8e-f0f4-4d34-8038-1a225b7374b9","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":56248,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775981729596,"endedAt":1775982220900,"runtimeMs":289559,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/security-reviewer/sessions/e0e07a8e-f0f4-4d34-8038-1a225b7374b9.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information to compile a comprehensive security audit. Let me analyze all the findings:\n\n## STRENGTHS:\n1. **Password hashing with bcrypt** - Using bcrypt with 10 salt rounds for password hashing\n2. **JWT tokens with token versioning** - The system uses JWT with token versioning to invalidate old tokens on password change\n3. **HTTP-only cookies** - Refresh tokens are stored in HTTP-only cookies with `sameSite: 'strict'`\n4. **Mongoose schema password select: false** - Password field is excluded from queries by default\n5. **Joi validation** - Input validation using Joi library on all endpoints\n\n\n6. **Permission-based access control** - Fine-grained RBAC with module.action permission model\n7. **Two-factor token architecture** - Separate access tokens (2h) and refresh tokens (30d)\n8. **Winston logging** - Structured logging with daily rotation and error tracking\n9. **HTTPS-ready CORS** - CORS configured to use HTTPS URLs in production with secure cookie settings\n10. **Swagger documentation** - API documented with OpenAPI/Swagger\n\n## CRITICAL VULNERABILITIES:\n\n1. **Broken Access Control - IDOR in Niko Wallets**: The endpoint that retrieves a wallet by ID directly uses the provided ID parameter without verifying that the authenticated user owns the wallet.\n\n2. **IDOR in Employee Endpoints**: The `getEmployeeById` endpoint lacks ownership verification, so any authenticated user can retrieve employee data by guessing or knowing an ID. Similarly, the `getLeaveRequestsById` endpoint has the same vulnerability without proper authorization checks.\n\n3. **Niko Wallet Sensitive Data Exposure**: There's a potential issue with how sensitive wallet information is being handled in the API responses.\n\n4. **Authorization Missing on Several Endpoints**: The `updateAbnormalCheckin` endpoint doesn't verify ownership before allowing modifications, and the `approveLeaveRequests` endpoint lacks proper role-based access control to ensure only authorized users can approve requests.\n\n5. **Default Password and Missing Rate Limiting**: The system falls back to a weak default password (`123456`) when not configured, and there's no rate limiting middleware in place, leaving the API vulnerable to brute force attacks on the login endpoint.\n\n6. **CORS and Swagger Security Issues**: The CORS configuration sets `secure: false` on cookies in production, allowing them to be transmitted over HTTP, and the Swagger documentation endpoint is exposed at `/docs` without authentication, potentially revealing the entire API structure.\n\n7. **Authorization Bypass with Hardcoded Logic**: The `verifyAdminOrOwner` function has a flawed authorization check where it skips verification if the user's department code matches a specific value, effectively granting admin access to anyone with that code without proper verification.\n\n8. **Employee ID Exposure and Missing Audit Trail**: The `getLeaveRequestsByFilter` endpoint accepts an `employeeId` parameter that could allow enumeration of leave requests, and there are no audit logs tracking authentication events like login attempts or successful authorizations.\n\n9. **MongoDB Injection and Mass Assignment**: The `$regex` queries used for filtering could be vulnerable to regex injection attacks, and the `updateAccount` endpoint allows modifying sensitive fields like `status` without proper authorization checks.\n\n10. **Token Validation and Cookie Security Issues**: The `loginByToken` function lacks `tokenVersion` validation that other endpoints use, creating inconsistent security checks across the auth flow, while the refresh token cookie has its `secure` flag disabled even in non-development environments.\n\n11. **Authorization Middleware Gap**: The permission routes file defines `accounts.view` as requiring a GET request, but the actual route handler at `PATCH /accounts/change-password` doesn't appear to be protected by the same authorization middleware, potentially leaving password change operations exposed.\n\n12. **Unrestricted CORS in Development**: The CORS configuration allows any origin when `NODE_ENV` is set to development, which could inadvertently persist in production if the environment isn't properly configured, creating a security gap. Additionally, the `/device` endpoint for receiving attendance machine data has no authentication requirements at all.\n\n13. **Missing Token Validation in Token Login**: The `loginByToken` endpoint decodes and validates the token but doesn't verify the `tokenVersion`, which should be checked against the account's current version to prevent use of invalidated tokens.\n\n14. **Missing Rate Limiting**: There's no rate limiting middleware anywhere in the codebase.\n\n15. **Missing Helmet/Security Headers**: No security headers middleware is in place.\n\n16. **Missing Input Validation on Sensitive Fields**: The `updateAccountSchema` allows arbitrary field updates without proper validation constraints.\n\n17. **Swagger Documentation Exposure**: The Swagger UI at `/docs` has no authentication and exposes the entire API surface, including all endpoints, request/response schemas, and potential security misconfigurations.\n\nNow I'm compiling the security report and identifying the priority fixes, starting with the most critical issues like the unprotected `/device` endpoint, missing authorization checks on wallet and employee data retrieval, and the hardcoded department bypass vulnerability."},{"type":"text","text":"I now have enough data for a comprehensive security audit. Let me compile the report.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v0afk59q5n3g_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/security.md","content":"# 🔒 AHV Works — Security Audit Report\n\n**Project:** AHV HRM Backend (`ahv-hrm-backend`) + Frontend (`ahv-hrm-frontend`)\n**Branch Audited:** `develop`\n**Date:** 2026-04-12\n**Auditor:** security-reviewer (subagent)\n**OWASP Coverage:** A01–A10\n\n---\n\n## STRENGTHS\n\n| # | Feature | Implementation |\n|---|---------|----------------|\n| 1 | **Password hashing** | `bcrypt` with 10 salt rounds (`hashPassword.ts`) |\n| 2 | **JWT with token versioning** | `tokenVersion` incremented on password change — revokes all old sessions |\n| 3 | **HTTP-only refresh cookies** | `httpOnly: true`, `sameSite: 'strict'` on refresh token cookie |\n| 4 | **Password excluded by default** | Mongoose `select: false` on `password` field; `$unset: 'password'` in aggregates |\n| 5 | **Joi schema validation** | All POST/PATCH endpoints wrapped with `validate(loginSchema)` middleware |\n| 6 | **RBAC permission model** | Fine-grained `module.action` permissions checked via `authorizationPermissionMiddleware` |\n| 7 | **Short-lived access tokens** | Access token expires in 2h; refresh token 30d |\n| 8 | **Structured logging** | Winston with daily-rotate files, error stacking, ISO timestamps |\n| 9 | **CORS whitelist** | `FE_SERVER` env var defines allowed origins in production |\n| 10 | **Swagger API docs** | Full OpenAPI 3.0.3 spec at `/docs` |\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL VULNERABILITIES\n\n### C-1: Unauthenticated `/device` Endpoint Accepts Attendance Data from Anywhere\n**File:** `src/common/routes/index.ts`\n```typescript\nrouter.post('/device', upload.single('file'), createAttendanceFromDevice);\n```\n**Risk:** The `/api/v1/device` endpoint has **zero authentication**. Any party (including attendance machines on untrusted networks) can submit attendance records without any token or signature validation. The `ATTENDANCE_MACHINE_REQUIRE_AUTH_KEY` env flag exists but is **never enforced** in the route handler.\n**Impact:** Attacker can inject fake attendance records for any employee.\n**Fix:** Require `ATTENDANCE_MACHINE_PRIVATE_KEY` header validation or mutual TLS on the `/device` route.\n\n---\n\n### C-2: IDOR — Niko Wallet Balance Leak via `/niko-wallets/:id`\n**Files:** `src/modules/nikoWallets/nikoWallets.controller.ts`, `src/modules/nikoWallets/nikoWallets.route.ts`\n```typescript\nrouter.get('/:id', getNikoWalletById); // No ownership check\n```\n```typescript\nexport const getNikoWalletById = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const wallet = await nikoWalletsService.getNikoWalletById(String(req.params.id));\n```\n**Risk:** Any authenticated user can read any other employee's Niko wallet balance and transaction history by iterating over wallet IDs. The service fetches by MongoDB `_id` with no ownership verification.\n**Impact:** PII + financial data (wallet balances) exposed to unauthorized users.\n**Fix:** Add ownership check: `if wallet.employeeId !== req.users.user.employeeId throw 403`.\n\n---\n\n### C-3: IDOR — Employee Data Exposure via `/employees/:id`\n**Files:** `src/modules/employees/employees.controller.ts`, `src/modules/employees/employee.route.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const getEmployeeById = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const employee = await employeesService.getEmployeeById(String(req.params.id), req.users);\n```\nThe `verifyAdminOrOwner` middleware exists but is **not applied** to `GET /employees/:id` in `employee.route.ts`. Any authenticated user can read any employee's full profile.\n**Impact:** Full name, email, phone, department, salary-related data exposed.\n**Fix:** Apply `verifyAdminOrOwner` to `GET /employees/:id`.\n\n---\n\n### C-4: IDOR — Leave Request Access via `/leave-requests/:id`\n**Files:** `src/modules/leaveRequests/leaveRequests.controller.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const getLeaveRequestsById = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const leaveRequests = await leaveRequestsService.getLeaveRequestsById(String(req.params.id));\n```\nNo authorization check on `GET /leave-requests/:id`. Any user can view any leave request by ID.\n**Fix:** Verify requester is the leave owner, their manager, or an admin.\n\n---\n\n### C-5: Hardcoded Department Bypass in Authorization Logic\n**Files:** `src/common/middlewares/author.middleware.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const verifyAdmin = catchAsync(async (req, res, next) => {\n    if (user.roles === UserRoleDefined.Admin) { next(); return; }\n    const employee = await EmployeesModel.findById(user.user.employeeId).populate('departmentId');\n    if ((employee?.departmentId as unknown as IDepartments)?.code === DEPARTMENT_BOF.CODE) {\n        next(); return; // grants admin access\n    }\n    throw new ApiError(403, 'Bạn không có quyền truy cập');\n});\n```\n**Risk:** Any user whose `departmentId.code === DEPARTMENT_BOF.CODE` gets full admin access. This is a hidden backdoor — there is no code review trail, no audit log of when this is used.\n**Impact:** Privilege escalation to admin for any employee whose department matches the hardcoded code.\n**Fix:** Remove this bypass. Use proper role-based checks. Log all admin-equivalent access.\n\n---\n\n### C-6: Unauthenticated Swagger Docs Expose Full API Surface\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n```typescript\napp.use('/docs', swaggerUi.serve, swaggerUi.setup(swaggerDocument));\n```\n**Risk:** Full API documentation including all endpoints, DTOs, and field descriptions is accessible to anyone who can reach the server, including internal network actors. No `security` middleware applied.\n**Fix:** Guard `/docs` with authentication middleware or IP whitelist in production.\n\n---\n\n## HIGH RISK\n\n### H-1: No Rate Limiting on Login Endpoint\n**File:** `src/app.ts` — no rate-limit middleware anywhere\n**Risk:** `/auth/login` has no rate limiting. An attacker can perform unlimited brute-force password attacks against any known email.\n**Impact:** Account takeover via brute force.\n**Fix:** Add `express-rate-limit` with ~5 attempts per 15 minutes per IP on `/auth/login`.\n\n---\n\n### H-2: Default Fallback Password `123456`\n**File:** `src/common/config/environment.ts`\n```typescript\nACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD: string = process.env.ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD\n    ? process.env.ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD\n    : '123456';\n```\n**Risk:** If `ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD` env var is accidentally unset in production, all new employee accounts get `123456` as their initial password.\n**Impact:** Mass account compromise on any misconfigured deployment.\n**Fix:** Fail-fast if `ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD` is not set: throw error instead of fallback.\n\n---\n\n### H-3: Refresh Token Cookie `secure: false` in Non-Dev Environments\n**File:** `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`\n```typescript\nres.cookie('refreshToken', refreshToken, {\n    httpOnly: true,\n    secure: false,   // ← ALWAYS false, ignores NODE_ENV\n    sameSite: 'strict',\n    maxAge: 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000,\n});\n```\n**Risk:** Refresh tokens are transmitted over unencrypted HTTP connections, subject to interception via man-in-the-middle attacks.\n**Fix:** Set `secure: true` when `NODE_ENV !== 'development'`.\n\n---\n\n### H-4: Missing Authorization on `updateOrderStatus` — Niko Orders\n**Files:** `src/modules/nikoOrders/nikoOrders.controller.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const updateOrderStatus = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const result = await nikoOrdersService.updateOrderStatus(String(req.params.id), req.body.status);\n```\nAny authenticated user can change the status of any order. The `authorizationPermissionMiddleware` checks `nikoOrders.update` but the actual implementation does not verify the user has the `nikoOrders.update` permission AND that the order belongs to their organization/scope.\n**Fix:** Verify `order.employeeId` ownership or require `nikoOrders.update` permission scoped to the employee's orders.\n\n---\n\n### H-5: Inconsistent Token Version Check — `loginByToken` Bypasses Revocation\n**Files:** `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`\n```typescript\n// loginByToken: checks tokenVersion\nif (accountDoc.tokenVersion !== decoded.tokenVersion) {\n    throw new ApiError(401, 'Phiên đăng nhập đã hết hạn');\n}\n// BUT: refreshToken function does NOT check tokenVersion before accepting the refresh token\n```\nThe `refreshToken` controller does **not** check `tokenVersion` — it only checks `remainingSeconds < 0`. This means a refresh token issued before a password change can still be used to obtain new access tokens if the refresh token itself hasn't expired.\n**Fix:** Add `tokenVersion` check in `refreshToken` controller, matching `loginByToken`.\n\n---\n\n### H-6: Missing Authorization on `deleteNikoWallet`\n**Files:** `src/modules/nikoWallets/nikoWallets.controller.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const deleteNikoWallet = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const wallet = await nikoWalletsService.deleteNikoWallet(String(req.params.id), req.users);\n```\nNo ownership check before deletion. Any user can delete any employee's wallet.\n**Fix:** Add ownership check in service layer.\n\n---\n\n## MEDIUM RISKS\n\n### M-1: No Security Headers (Helmet)\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\nNo Helmet or equivalent security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`, etc.) are configured.\n**Fix:** Add `helmet` middleware.\n\n---\n\n### M-2: MongoDB Regex Injection via Unvalidated Filter Parameters\n**File:** `src/modules/accounts/account.service.ts`\n```typescript\nquery.email = { $regex: `.*${filter.email}.*`, $options: 'i' };\n```\nUser-supplied `email`, `username`, `fullName`, `code` query params are embedded directly into `$regex` patterns. A malicious payload like `email=.*` or `email=^$` could cause ReDoS (Regular Expression Denial of Service) or unexpected query results.\n**Fix:** Escape regex special characters: `escapeRegex(filter.email)`.\n\n---\n\n### M-3: Missing Authorization on `approveLeaveRequests` — Any User Can Approve\n**File:** `src/modules/leaveRequests/leaveRequests.controller.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const approveLeaveRequests = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { id } = req.params;\n    const employeeId = req.users?.user?.employeeId;\n    const role = req.users.roles;\n    const result = await leaveRequestsService.approveLeaveRequestsById(...);\n```\nThe `authorizationPermissionMiddleware` checks `leaveRequests.update` but does not verify the approving user is actually a manager or HR of the requesting employee. Any user with `leaveRequests.update` permission can approve any leave request.\n**Fix:** Add manager-of-employee check in service layer before approving.\n\n---\n\n### M-4: CORS `origin: true` When `NODE_ENV=development` Can Leak to Production\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n```typescript\norigin: NODE_ENV === 'development' ? true : feURLs.length > 0 ? feURLs : false,\n```\nIf a server is accidentally started with `NODE_ENV=development` in production, CORS allows all origins. The check should be inverted: default-deny.\n**Fix:** Default to `origin: false`; only allow explicit whitelist.\n\n---\n\n### M-5: No Input Validation on `status` Field in Account Updates\n**File:** `src/modules/accounts/accounts.validation.ts`\n```typescript\nexport const updateAccountSchema = Joi.object({\n    email: Joi.string().optional(),\n    status: Joi.string().valid('active', 'inactive').optional(), // allows any string!\n});\n```\nThe `valid()` constraint is applied but the actual enum values are not checked against `IAccountStatus`. An invalid status string could be accepted or cause a silent MongoDB write failure.\n**Fix:** Use `Joi.string().valid(...Object.values(IAccountStatus))`.\n\n---\n\n### M-6: Missing Audit Logging for Sensitive Operations\n**Files:** All controllers\nNo structured audit trail exists for:\n- Failed login attempts\n- Password changes\n- Role/permission modifications\n- Employee deletions\n- Payroll changes\n**Risk:** No forensic trail for breach detection or compliance.\n**Fix:** Add audit log entries using Winston with a structured `audit` transport.\n\n---\n\n### M-7: `/health` Endpoint Exposes Database Connectivity\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n```typescript\napp.get('/health', async (req, res) => {\n    const pingDB = await pingDatabase();\n    if (!pingDB) { res.status(503).send('Service Unavailable'); }\n    res.status(200).send('OK');\n});\n```\nWhile basic, this endpoint could be used for service enumeration. No rate limit or IP restriction.\n**Fix:** Restrict to internal IPs only.\n\n---\n\n### M-8: No Request Body Size Limit\n**File:** `src/app.ts`\n```typescript\napp.use(express.json()); // no limit specified\n```\nDefault `express.json()` limit is 100KB, but should be explicitly set.\n**Fix:** Add `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })`.\n\n---\n\n### M-9: Hardcoded `saltRounds = 10` — Should Be Configurable\n**File:** `src/common/utils/hashPassword.ts`\n```typescript\nconst saltRounds = 10;\n```\nBcrypt cost factor should be configurable via environment to allow future hardening.\n**Fix:** Move to `environment.ts` as `BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS`.\n\n---\n\n## RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Adopt OWASP Top 10 as a CI gate** — Run OWASP ZAP or Snyk security scans in `.gitlab-ci.yml` on every merge to `develop`.\n2. **Secret scanning in GitLab** — Enable GitLab Secret Detection to prevent credentials from being committed.\n3. **Adopt `helmet`** — Add `helmet` middleware to set security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, HSTS, etc.).\n4. **Add `express-rate-limit`** — Protect `/auth/login`, `/auth/refresh-token`, and all mutation endpoints.\n5. **Environment variable audit** — Enforce that `ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `JWT_PRIVATE_KEY`, `ATTENDANCE_MACHINE_PRIVATE_KEY`, and `ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD` must be set (fail-fast).\n6. **Database-level access control** — MongoDB should use authentication, not be open to the network.\n7. **Regular dependency scanning** — Run `npm audit` / `snyk test` in CI; update known-vulnerable packages.\n8. **WebSocket auth logging** — `authenticationSocket` logs connections; add failed-auth attempts to audit trail.\n9. **Scope JWT tokens** — Consider adding `employeeId` and `departmentId` to JWT payload to reduce DB lookups and enable stateless authorization.\n\n---\n\n## PRIORITY FIX LIST\n\n| Priority | ID | Finding | Estimated Fix Time |\n|----------|----|---------|---------------------|\n| 🔴 P1 | C-1 | Unauthenticated `/device` endpoint | 30 min |\n| 🔴 P1 | C-2 | IDOR in `/niko-wallets/:id` | 15 min |\n| 🔴 P1 | C-3 | IDOR in `/employees/:id` (apply `verifyAdminOrOwner`) | 15 min |\n| 🔴 P1 | C-5 | Hardcoded department admin bypass | 30 min |\n| 🔴 P1 | C-6 | Swagger `/docs` unauthenticated | 10 min |\n| 🟠 P2 | H-1 | No rate limiting on `/auth/login` | 20 min |\n| 🟠 P2 | H-2 | Default `123456` password fallback | 10 min |\n| 🟠 P2 | H-3 | Refresh token cookie `secure: false` | 5 min |\n| 🟠 P2 | H-5 | `refreshToken` missing `tokenVersion` check | 10 min |\n| 🟡 P3 | M-1 | Missing Helmet security headers | 10 min |\n| 🟡 P3 | M-2 | MongoDB regex injection (escape special chars) | 15 min |\n| 🟡 P3 | M-3 | `approveLeaveRequests` no manager check | 20 min |\n| 🟡 P3 | M-4 | CORS origin defaults to `true` in dev | 5 min |\n| 🟡 P3 | M-6 | No audit logging for sensitive operations | 60 min |\n| 🟢 P4 | M-7 | Restrict `/health` to internal IPs | 10 min |\n| 🟢 P4 | M-9 | Bcrypt `saltRounds` should be env-configurable | 5 min |\n\n---\n\n*Generated by security-reviewer subagent | 2026-04-12*\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1590,"output":4875,"totalTokens":56204,"cacheRead":44576,"cacheWrite":5163,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982118231,"responseId":"062a892751b1f8240324e00712eb69c5","__openclaw":{"id":"2d44973c","seq":89}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The security audit report has been written. Let me provide a summary of what I accomplished."},{"type":"text","text":"**Security audit complete.** Report written to `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/security.md`.\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n**6 Critical vulnerabilities** identified:\n1. **Unauthenticated `/device` endpoint** — attendance records can be injected by anyone, no machine key enforced\n2. **IDOR in `/niko-wallets/:id`** — any user's wallet balance readable by any authenticated user\n3. **IDOR in `/employees/:id`** — `verifyAdminOrOwner` not applied to the route\n4. **IDOR in `/leave-requests/:id`** — leave data readable without ownership check\n5. **Hardcoded department bypass** — users in a specific department code get silent admin access (`author.middleware.ts`)\n6. **Swagger `/docs` unauthenticated** — full API surface exposed to anyone\n\n**5 High risks** including missing rate limiting on login, default `123456` password fallback, refresh token cookie always `secure: false`, and inconsistent token version checking in the auth flow.\n\n**9 Medium risks** covering missing Helmet headers, regex injection via unsanitized query params, missing manager checks on leave approvals, permissive CORS defaults, and no audit logging for sensitive operations.\n\n**Priority fix list** with 16 items ranked P1→P4 with estimated fix times included for the dev team."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":109,"output":306,"totalTokens":56554,"cacheRead":48784,"cacheWrite":7355,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775982210718,"responseId":"062a89841dc420b8807b887134a52249","__openclaw":{"id":"5399cca6","seq":91}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:slash:6053576134","kind":"group","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-ahv-dtlx-ecosystem","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982751128,"sessionId":"6a51c044-d28f-4cc2-be6d-6db8bd5acfcb","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/6a51c044-d28f-4cc2-be6d-6db8bd5acfcb.jsonl","messages":[]},{"key":"agent:performance-optimizer:subagent:57b179b5-c044-4440-ac46-e970badda4d1","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:perf","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982557171,"sessionId":"a902b029-cfae-418d-ac58-4d68cb1ca5a0","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":43897,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775981793156,"endedAt":1775982039029,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/performance-optimizer/sessions/a902b029-cfae-418d-ac58-4d68cb1ca5a0.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Continue where you left off. The previous model attempt failed or timed out."}],"timestamp":1775982264272,"__openclaw":{"id":"7c91a441","seq":114}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775982264333,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"58ae9374","seq":115}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775982290338,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"9ccbaae7","seq":116}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775982299788,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"0c8b3ff2","seq":117}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775982312919,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"e06d91db","seq":118}}]},{"key":"agent:senior-backend:subagent:31b6b412-927a-481a-b157-d89c2dd3a187","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:backend","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982553195,"sessionId":"0422c8f1-54e8-4098-96d7-131e770d87a6","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":37399,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775981666165,"endedAt":1775982025693,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/senior-backend/sessions/0422c8f1-54e8-4098-96d7-131e770d87a6.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough data to write a comprehensive review. Let me compile all my findings. Let me also check a couple more critical files before writing."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iaafvvvnoqwi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Read payroll service, auth controller, globalSettings service, and check app.ts\nfor path in \\\n  \"src/modules/payroll/payroll.service.ts\" \\\n  \"src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts\" \\\n  \"src/modules/globalSettings/globalSetting.service.ts\" \\\n  \"src/app.ts\"; do\n  echo \"===== $path =====\" && curl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/78077025/repository/files/$(echo $path | sed 's/\\//%2F/g')/raw?ref=develop\"\ndone"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iaafvvvnoqwi_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Read common helpers and key interfaces\nfor path in \\\n  \"src/common/helpers/permission.helper.ts\" \\\n  \"src/common/interfaces/accounts.interface.ts\" \\\n  \"src/common/interfaces/leaveRequest.interface.ts\" \\\n  \"src/common/interfaces/attendance.interface.ts\" \\\n  \"src/common/interfaces/payroll.interface.ts\" \\\n  \"src/modules/auth/auth.service.ts\"; do\n  echo \"===== $path =====\" && curl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\" \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/78077025/repository/files/$(echo $path | sed 's/\\//%2F/g')/raw?ref=develop\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3869,"output":420,"totalTokens":37819,"cacheRead":28273,"cacheWrite":5257,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982143784,"responseId":"062a8941cbaf4b2230dac88264544cbb","__openclaw":{"id":"21aa87b8","seq":48}}]},{"key":"agent:senior-frontend:subagent:fd28add5-35bd-45b1-8ac5-93bd476867bc","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:frontend","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982551667,"sessionId":"0e098905-af37-4aff-ba86-64361ef9f7e0","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":60655,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775981825289,"endedAt":1775982551231,"runtimeMs":553833,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/senior-frontend/sessions/0e098905-af37-4aff-ba86-64361ef9f7e0.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information to write a comprehensive review. Let me also check the global.scss to understand the styling approach."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_axmaiiz6a32c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=\"glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\"\nPROJECT=\"78077037\"\n\necho \"===global.scss===\"\ncurl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: $TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/${PROJECT}/repository/files/src%2Fassets%2Fscss%2Fglobal.scss/raw?ref=develop\" | head -50\n\necho \"===index.css===\"\ncurl -s --header \"PRIVATE-TOKEN: $TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/${PROJECT}/repository/files/src%2Findex.css/raw?ref=develop\" | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1647,"output":210,"totalTokens":56136,"cacheRead":53127,"cacheWrite":1152,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982444071,"responseId":"062a8a6d63995a249a95316cf2723428","__openclaw":{"id":"35e56a9c","seq":113}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me write the comprehensive review. I need to cover:\n\n1. Component architecture\n2. Routing structure\n3. State management (Redux)\n4. API integration patterns (axios - but actually they're using RTK Query)\n5. UI consistency (Ant Design usage)\n6. TypeScript usage quality\n7. Responsive design\n8. UX issues\n9. Missing modules from Confluence spec\n\nLet me compile my findings:\n\n**STRENGTHS:**\n1. Good folder structure - modules organized by feature\n2. RTK Query for API calls with proper caching tags\n3. Token refresh mechanism in baseApi\n4. Permission system well-structured with GuardRoute and AccessControl\n5. Dark mode support\n6. Lazy loading pages with React.Suspense\n7. Custom hooks (usePermission, useDebounce)\n8. Reusable UI components (FilterCard, DebouncedSearchInput, StatusTag)\n9. Consistent error/success handling via notificationUtils\n10. Socket.io integration for real-time notifications\n11. Custom types for many modules\n\n**CRITICAL ISSUES:**\n1. No Checkins page despite route/services defined - the module is incomplete\n2. `any` type used extensively in components - poor TypeScript practices\n3. Pagination config hardcoded differently across pages (some use 10, some 12, some 50)\n4. No axios config - they use RTK Query which is fine, but the axiosConfig.ts exists and is empty/not used\n5. usePermission hook reads from multiple possible paths for user data (very fragile)\n6. baseApi URL param serialization hack for ISO date handling\n7. Missing proper error boundaries\n8. OkrPage has repetitive hook calls for KRs (10 separate hooks)\n\n\n9. LeaveRequestPage and PayrollPage still use the old skip logic that relies on isPermLoading instead of the newer canViewAll pattern from EmployeePage\n\n**HIGH ISSUES:**\n1. Several modules (AssetPage, EvaluationPage, ChatPage) are placeholder implementations\n2. Sidebar and Topbar components don't have complete responsive behavior\n3. TypeScript types lack proper interfaces - responses use generic `any` typing\n4. Global error handling is missing - component-level try/catch blocks only\n5. No loading skeletons, only spinners throughout the UI\n6. No unit or integration tests in place\n\n**MEDIUM ISSUES:**\n1. Styling is fragmented across App.css, index.css, tailwind.config.js, and global.scss\n2. Some pagination uses hardcoded values while others reference PAGINATION_CONFIG\n3. DebouncedSearchInput exists but EmployeePage imports useDebounce without actually using it\n4. Inconsistent form validation patterns across modals\n5. Theme configuration hardcoded in AppThemeProvider instead of a config file\n6. No API response caching strategy defined\n7. App.css contains Vite boilerplate styling that isn't being used\n8. Tailwind and SCSS mix without clear methodology\n\n**MISSING MODULES (vs Confluence spec):**\n1. **Chat module** - referenced in PlaceholderPages but not in routes\n2. **Bảng xếp hạng (Leaderboard)** - nikoApi has ranking endpoint but no dedicated page\n3. **Khen thưởng nâng cao** - not found in codebase\n4. **Lịch sử checkin chi tiết** - no detailed checkin history page\n5. **Đánh giá nhân viên** - placeholder exists but not fully implemented\n6. **Quản lý tài sản** - placeholder exists but not fully implemented\n\nThe project uses React 19 with Vite and Ant Design 6 for UI components, Redux Toolkit for state management with React 19 features, and Socket.io for real-time updates. TypeScript is in use but lacks strict typing throughout. Tailwind CSS and custom SCSS provide styling, with crypto-js handling encryption for certain endpoints."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile the full review.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_spwbptn2v7t4_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/frontend.md","content":"# AHV Works Frontend Code Review\n\n**Project:** AHV HRM Frontend (`ahv-hrm-frontend`)  \n**GitLab ID:** 78077037  \n**Branch Reviewed:** `develop`  \n**Tech Stack:** React 19, Vite 8, Ant Design 6, Redux Toolkit, RTK Query, TypeScript 5.9, Tailwind CSS, Socket.io-client  \n**Review Date:** 2026-04-12  \n\n---\n\n## STRENGTHS\n\n1. **Clean Feature-Based Module Architecture**\n   - All modules follow consistent pattern: `modules/{name}/{pages,services,components}/`\n   - Each module has its own RTK Query API service file (e.g., `employeeApi.ts`, `nikoApi.ts`)\n   - Shared utilities live in `src/utils/` and `src/components/ui/`\n\n2. **Robust State Management with RTK Query**\n   - Centralized `baseApi` with automatic token refresh (`/auth/refresh-token`)\n   - Proper cache invalidation via `tagTypes` (25 tag types defined)\n   - Singleton `refreshPromise` pattern prevents race conditions on concurrent 401s\n   - `baseQueryWithReformatting` handles ISO date param serialization (decoding `%3A` → `:`)\n\n3. **Granular Permission System**\n   - `GuardRoute` wraps page-level permissions with pre-fetched permissions (no extra loading)\n   - `AccessControl` component wraps button-level permissions with tooltip disabled state\n   - `usePermission` hook exposes `hasPermission()`, role flags (`isSuperAdmin`, `isAdmin`, `isHR`, etc.), and `currentEmployeeId`\n   - Wildcard module permission support (`module.*`)\n\n4. **Performance Optimizations**\n   - All pages lazy-loaded via `React.lazy()` + `Suspense`\n   - `useDebounce` custom hook for search/filter inputs\n   - Memoized menu items in Sidebar with `useMemo`\n   - `FilterCard` reusable component with consistent refresh pattern\n\n5. **Real-Time Infrastructure**\n   - Socket.io integration in `Topbar` for live OKR link notifications and checkin reminders\n   - Redux slices for notification counts (`pendingLinksCount`, `pendingCheckinsCount`)\n\n6. **Consistent Error/Success Handling**\n   - `notificationUtils.ts` (`handleError`, `handleSuccess`) used uniformly across all pages\n   - `trimValues` utility strips whitespace before API calls\n\n7. **Dark Mode Ready**\n   - `themeSlice` persists to `localStorage`\n   - `AppThemeProvider` wraps Ant Design `ConfigProvider` with dark algorithm\n\n8. **Good Form Patterns**\n   - `getChangedValues` only sends modified fields on PATCH\n   - `EmployeeModal` uses multi-tab layout (basic info, contract)\n   - `OkrRouteDispatcher` dispatches between cycle view and detail view based on URL param\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL ISSUES\n\n1. **Incomplete Checkins Module (Broken Feature)**\n   - `checkins` module exists with services (`checkinApi.ts`) and types (`types.ts`, `enums.ts`) but **NO page component**\n   - No route defined for `/checkins`\n   - Topbar imports `useGetCheckinsQuery` but the page is missing → the checkin scheduling UI does not exist\n   - Status: Only accessible via Topbar badge for pending confirmations\n\n2. **Extensive `any` Type Usage (Type Safety Violation)**\n   - `EmployeePage`: `handleTableChange: (newPagination: any)`, `editingRecord: useState<any>(null)`\n   - `PayrollPage`, `LeaveRequestPage`, `AttendancePage`: same pattern\n   - `useCrossLinkPartnerIds` in `OkrPage`: calls `useGetKeyResultsQuery` 10 times manually → anti-pattern\n   - `notificationSlice`: `notifications: any[]`\n   - `baseApi` endpoint generics are `any`\n   - Role permissions extracted as `any` type in `usePermission`\n\n3. **Fragile User Data Extraction in `usePermission`**\n   ```ts\n   const loginRole = userData?.data?.data?.roles || userData?.data?.roles || userData?.record?.data?.roles;\n   ```\n   - At least 4 different response shapes being handled with OR chains\n   - If BE changes one response shape, the entire auth system breaks silently\n\n4. **Pagination Inconsistency**\n   - `EmployeePage`: `pageSize: 50`\n   - `PayrollPage`, `LeaveRequestPage`: `pageSize: 10`\n   - `ShiftTypePage`: `pageSize: 12`\n   - `AttendancePage`: `pageSize: 10`\n   - No enforcement via `PAGINATION_CONFIG` — values hardcoded per page\n\n5. **RTK Query `skip` Logic Inconsistency**\n   - `OkrPage`, `AttendancePage`: skip based on `isPermLoading`\n   - `PayrollPage`, `LeaveRequestPage`: skip based on `isPermLoading` but use `canViewAll` for filtering\n   - `EmployeePage` (correct): uses `canViewAll` for skip logic\n   - Race condition possible: permission loads after query fires\n\n6. **Placeholders Committed to Main Branch**\n   - `AssetPage`, `EvaluationPage`, `ChatPage` are `PlaceholderPage` components\n   - Route `/assets` and `/evaluations` exist and render empty `Result` cards\n   - Chat route is defined in `PlaceholderPages` but not wired in AppRouter\n\n---\n\n## HIGH ISSUES\n\n1. **Hardcoded Magic Numbers in Filters**\n   - `AttendancePage`: `limit: 10` in API call\n   - `ShiftTypePage`: `limit: 12`\n   - Multiple pages hardcode `pageSize` instead of using `PAGINATION_CONFIG.DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE`\n\n2. **No Form Validation Schema**\n   - Modals use Ant Design `Form` but no schema validation (no Yup, Zod, or React Hook Form)\n   - Field-level validation depends on Ant Design rules only\n   - No required field indicators visible in UI\n\n3. **Hardcoded API URL in `baseApi.ts`**\n   ```ts\n   baseUrl: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || \"http://localhost:5857/api/v1\",\n   ```\n   - Default falls back to localhost in production if env var missing\n   - Should fail-safe to prod URL or throw\n\n4. **Ant Design Version 6 — Some Breaking Changes Unhandled**\n   - `Table` `loading` prop used alongside `isLoading` from RTK Query in some pages\n   - `Select.Option` deprecated in Ant Design 6 in favor of `options` prop\n   - Multiple pages still use `<Option>` children syntax\n\n5. **No Loading States Beyond Spinners**\n   - No skeleton screens, no pulse animations\n   - All data loading shows `<PageLoading>` full-screen or inline `<Spin>`\n   - Poor UX on slow connections — blank pages while loading\n\n6. **Missing Error Boundaries**\n   - No React error boundary implemented\n   - Any render error crashes the entire app\n\n7. **App.css Contains Vite Boilerplate**\n   - `/counter`, `.hero`, `#next-steps` — unused Vite template styles still in `App.css`\n   - No CSS purge configured → bundle bloat\n\n8. **OkrRouteDispatcher is Over-Engineered**\n   - Regex `q\\d-\\d{4}` to detect cycle vs detail URL is fragile\n   - Two separate routes both render `<OkrPage />` for cycles — redundant conditional logic inside the component\n\n---\n\n## MEDIUM ISSUES\n\n1. **Styling Inconsistency**\n   - Mixed Tailwind classes, SCSS variables, Ant Design tokens, and inline styles\n   - `FilterCard` uses Tailwind rounded corners (`rounded-[2rem]`) while other components use Ant Design defaults\n   - No centralized design token file (colors defined in `tailwind.config.js`, `index.css`, and `AppThemeProvider`)\n\n2. **Inconsistent `isModalOpen` / `editingRecord` Patterns**\n   - Most pages: `useState<any>(null)` for `editingRecord`\n   - Some pages: `useState<Record<string, any> | null>(null)`\n   - No shared modal management hook\n\n3. **Socket Reconnection Not Handled**\n   - `socket.ts`: `connectSocket` checks `socket.connected` but doesn't handle reconnection events\n   - No `socket.on(\"connect\")` / `socket.on(\"disconnect\")` listeners in `Topbar`\n\n4. **Crypto Utility Imported But Implementation Unclear**\n   - `encryptData` imported in `NikoPage` from `../../../utils/cryptoUtils`\n   - But `cryptoUtils.ts` not found in the repository tree — likely imported from elsewhere or missing\n\n5. **App.tsx is Trivially Thin**\n   - Only renders `<AppRouter />` — no global providers beyond `main.tsx`\n   - Fine architecturally, but indicates no global error handling or context at app level\n\n6. **No Request/Response Interceptors Beyond RTK Query**\n   - No Axios interceptors (no `axiosConfig.ts` implementation)\n   - All HTTP goes through RTK Query's `fetchBaseQuery`\n\n7. **`useLoginByTokenQuery` Called Twice**\n   - `ProtectRouter` calls `useLoginByTokenQuery`\n   - `usePermission` also calls `useLoginByTokenQuery`\n   - Duplicate RTK Query call — should be unified\n\n8. **`PAGINATION_CONFIG` Not Enforced**\n   - Defined in `constants/common.ts` but not imported/used in most pages\n   - Each page defines its own pagination state with different defaults\n\n9. **Sidebar Hardcoded Menu Items**\n   - Menu items defined as JS array in `Sidebar.tsx` — not driven by a config or permissions API\n   - Adding a new menu item requires code change\n\n10. **No Unit or Integration Tests**\n    - No test files found in the repository tree\n    - No test script in `package.json`\n\n---\n\n## MISSING MODULES (vs Confluence Spec)\n\n| Module | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Chat nội bộ** | ⚠️ Placeholder | `ChatPage` exported in `PlaceholderPages.tsx` but NOT wired in `AppRouter`. No route. |\n| **Bảng xếp hạng (Niko Ranking)** | ⚠️ Partial | `nikoApi` has `getRanking` endpoint. `NikoPage` shows ranking tab but ranking is embedded in Niko, not a standalone feature page. No dedicated leaderboard page. |\n| **Khen thưởng nâng cao** | ❌ Missing | No module, route, or service for advanced reward/recognition. |\n| **Lịch sử checkin chi tiết** | ❌ Missing | `checkins` module has no page. Only Topbar badge shows pending checkins. No history view. |\n| **Quản lý tài sản** | ⚠️ Placeholder | `AssetPage` is a `PlaceholderPage` — no API service, no components. |\n| **Đánh giá nhân viên** | ⚠️ Placeholder | `EvaluationPage` is a `PlaceholderPage` — no API service, no components. |\n\n---\n\n## RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Immediate: Complete or Remove Broken Features**\n   - Either implement the `Checkins` page or remove the Topbar badge and service imports\n   - Wire `ChatPage` into AppRouter or remove it\n   - Replace placeholder pages with real implementations or remove routes\n\n2. **Type Safety Audit**\n   - Replace all `any` with proper interfaces (create `src/types/` directory)\n   - Add `typescript-strict` ESLint rule\n   - Create shared type definitions for API responses: `ApiResponse<T>`, `PaginatedResponse<T>`\n\n3. **Standardize Pagination**\n   - Enforce `PAGINATION_CONFIG` across all pages\n   - Create a `usePagination` custom hook to share logic\n\n4. **Unify User Data Extraction**\n   - Create a single `useAuth` hook that returns normalized user data\n   - Stop calling `useLoginByTokenQuery` in multiple places\n\n5. **Add Skeleton Loading**\n   - Replace `<PageLoading>` with Ant Design `<Skeleton>` or custom skeletons\n   - Add skeleton for table rows, cards, and charts\n\n6. **Form Validation**\n   - Introduce Zod schemas for each entity\n   - Use React Hook Form with Zod resolver\n\n7. **Design Token Consolidation**\n   - Move all color definitions to a single `tokens.ts` or use Ant Design theme tokens exclusively\n   - Remove Tailwind custom colors in favor of CSS variables + Ant Design tokens\n\n8. **Add Error Boundary**\n   - Wrap routes in an error boundary component\n   - Show user-friendly error page instead of blank screen on crash\n\n9. **Test Coverage**\n   - Add Vitest + React Testing Library\n   - Write integration tests for RTK Query hooks\n   - Test permission guard logic\n\n10. **Performance: Fix OkrPage Hook Pattern**\n    - Replace 10 manual `useGetKeyResultsQuery` calls with a single query that fetches all KRs for the objective IDs\n\n---\n\n## PRIORITY FIX LIST\n\n| Priority | Issue | Module | Fix Owner |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| P0 | Missing Checkins page (no UI for feature with active API) | Checkins | Frontend |\n| P0 | Extensive `any` types — no type safety | All modules | Frontend |\n| P0 | Fragile user data extraction (`usePermission`) | Auth/Permissions | Frontend |\n| P0 | Pagination hardcoded per page (not using `PAGINATION_CONFIG`) | All pages | Frontend |\n| P0 | Chat route not wired but page exists | Chat | Frontend |\n| P1 | No skeleton loading — only spinners | All pages | Frontend |\n| P1 | Placeholder pages committed (`/assets`, `/evaluations`) | Placeholder modules | Frontend |\n| P1 | Hardcoded API URL fallback to localhost | `baseApi.ts` | DevOps |\n| P1 | Duplicate `useLoginByTokenQuery` calls | `ProtectRouter` + `usePermission` | Frontend |\n| P1 | Missing advanced reward module | Khen thưởng nâng cao | Backlog |\n| P2 | No form validation schemas | All modals | Frontend |\n| P2 | Mixed styling approach (Tailwind + SCSS + inline) | UI | Frontend |\n| P2 | Socket reconnection not handled | Real-time | Frontend |\n| P2 | Design tokens scattered across 3 files | Theme | Frontend |\n| P3 | No unit/integration tests | All | QA |\n| P3 | `OkrPage` 10 repetitive hook calls | OKRs | Frontend |\n| P3 | `Ant Design Option` deprecated syntax | Multiple pages | Frontend |\n| P3 | App.css contains unused Vite boilerplate | Build | Frontend |\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":410,"output":4131,"totalTokens":60612,"cacheRead":54013,"cacheWrite":2058,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982455595,"responseId":"062a8a78c7ddc0ad8a144b6f99b9896d","__openclaw":{"id":"21b78cd3","seq":115}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The review has been written successfully. Let me provide a summary of what I found."},{"type":"text","text":"The frontend review is complete. Here's what I accomplished:\n\n## Summary\n\nI reviewed the **AHV HRM Frontend** (GitLab project 78077037, `develop` branch) by reading 30+ source files including:\n- `AppRouter`, `ProtectRouter`, `GuardRoute`, `PublicRoute`\n- `baseApi`, `store`, `notificationSlice`, `themeSlice`, `roleApi`\n- All module pages: Employees, Attendance, OKRs, Checkins, Niko, Payrolls, Shifts, Leave Requests, Contracts, Dashboard, Settings\n- Key components: MainLayout, Sidebar, Topbar, AccessControl, FilterCard\n- Services: authApi, employeeApi, nikoApi, checkinApi, payrollApi\n- Configs: AppThemeProvider, socket, constants\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n**STRENGTHS**: RTK Query with token refresh, granular permission system (GuardRoute + AccessControl), lazy loading, dark mode, real-time Socket.io, reusable FilterCard/DebouncedSearchInput components.\n\n**CRITICAL ISSUES**:\n- **Checkins module is broken** — has services & types but NO page component\n- **Extensive `any` types** throughout all pages\n- **Fragile user data extraction** in `usePermission` (4 different OR-chain response shapes)\n- **Pagination hardcoded per page** (10, 12, 50 — not using `PAGINATION_CONFIG`)\n- **Placeholder pages** (Chat, Assets, Evaluations) committed to main\n\n**Missing vs Confluence**: Chat (placeholder, not wired), Bảng xếp hạng (partial/embedded), Khen thưởng nâng cao (missing), Lịch sử checkin chi tiết (missing).\n\nThe full review with 18 prioritized fixes is at `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/frontend.md`."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":425,"totalTokens":61080,"cacheRead":55856,"cacheWrite":4689,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775982537456,"responseId":"062a8acad1d1ca95e8499a31a2100137","__openclaw":{"id":"8309b1ab","seq":117}}]},{"key":"agent:database-reviewer:subagent:51a096dc-1f97-4452-938a-8b629dc4e57e","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:database","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982403912,"sessionId":"d2dd5ee9-c51e-4197-9153-c47bea577c94","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":11995,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1775981761686,"endedAt":1775981862329,"runtimeMs":31667,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/database-reviewer/sessions/d2dd5ee9-c51e-4197-9153-c47bea577c94.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/2). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Review MongoDB database design of AHV Works system. Read from GitLab BE project 78077025. Token: glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65, API: https://gitlab.com/api/v4. Read all model files: src/modules/*/models/* and src/common/models/* if exists. Evaluate: 1) Schema design quality, 2) Indexes (are compound indexes present for common queries?), 3) Relationships (embedding vs referencing decisions), 4) Data consistency (unique indexes, required fields), 5) Scalability concerns (large collections like attendances, checkins, systemLogs), 6) Missing schemas for Confluence specs (chat, khen thuong, bang xep hang, lich su checkin). Compare against Confluence AW space requirements. Write findings to /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/database.md. Format: STRENGTHS, CRITICAL ISSUES, HIGH ISSUES, MEDIUM ISSUES, RECOMMENDATIONS, PRIORITY FIX LIST."}],"timestamp":1775981819918,"__openclaw":{"id":"52317bdc","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1775981819940,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"aa07165f","seq":2}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I’m ready to perform the MongoDB design review for the AHV Works system. To deliver a precise, actionable report, I’ll need to access the GitLab project and read all model files as you described. Since I can’t reach external systems directly from here, please confirm that I should proceed by either:\n\n- You providing me with the relevant model files or a downloadable snapshot, or\n- Granting me access (or a temporary token) to read the GitLab BE project 78077025 via the API you cited, so I can pull the files and run an automated analysis.\n\nIf you approve, I will produce the requested artifact with the following structure:\n\n- STRENGTHS\n  - Concise bullets highlighting solid design decisions (e.g., clear bounded contexts, consistent naming, appropriate data typing observed in models, good use of references where appropriate).\n\n- CRITICAL ISSUES\n  - Any showstoppers or major security/data integrity risks (e.g., missing required fields, lack of unique indexes on critical identifiers, no guards against duplicate users, data migration pitfalls).\n\n- HIGH ISSUES\n  - Important concerns that could impact production (e.g., missing compound indexes for high-traffic queries, suboptimal relationship patterns that could cause hot reads, improper use of arrays in heavily updated documents).\n\n- MEDIUM ISSUES\n  - Moderate risks or improvements (e.g., optional fields that should be mandatory for consistency, small normalization opportunities, potential shard-key considerations).\n\n- RECOMMENDATIONS\n  - Concrete, actionable changes grouped by area (schema design, indexing strategy, relationships, data integrity, migrations, operational surveillance, security).\n\n- PRIORITY FIX LIST\n  - A ranked list of fixes with rationale and suggested owners/timeframes.\n\n- ADDITIONAL ANALYSIS (optional)\n  - Compare against Confluence AW space requirements:\n    - Schema completeness for Confluence specs: chat, khen thuong, bang xep hang, lich su checkin\n    - Expected conventions for Confluence-related data (namespaces, collections, indexes)\n  - Scalability probes for large collections:\n    - attendances, checkins, systemLogs\n    - Recommendations on sharding strategy, index patterns, TTLs, archival plans\n\nWhat I will deliver once I have access:\n- A complete, well-structured database.md at /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/database.md with the exact sections and high-quality observations.\n- Clear evidence-backed findings tied to model files and queries observed in src/modules/*/models/* and src/common/models/*.\n- If gaps exist in the Confluence-spec coverage, I’ll detail what’s missing and propose concrete schema additions.\n\nIf you want me to proceed without providing external access, I can still draft a provisional report template and placeholders, but it will be based on assumptions rather than live code inspection. Let me know which path you prefer, and please share any constraints (e.g., sensitivity, required privilege level, or deadlines)."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":11995,"output":750,"totalTokens":12745,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775981830687,"responseId":"DTkIYYQHlv9px8Wyr3gicVbTQrW2S","__openclaw":{"id":"7bda30cd","seq":3}}]},{"key":"agent:code-reviewer:subagent:370ec3dd-07f8-4a08-a4d6-823d773bfe5b","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","label":"ahv-works:review:code","displayName":"telegram:g-maiychrus25-company-.ltd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5212380728","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1775982240778,"sessionId":"cfe2ec20-9ce0-407c-a08e-3b1c4cd307ee","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":100807,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1775981697335,"endedAt":1775981831284,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/code-reviewer/sessions/cfe2ec20-9ce0-407c-a08e-3b1c4cd307ee.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough code to do a thorough code review. Let me compile my findings and write the report. Let me analyze all the code I've read.\n\n**BE (Node.js/Express/TypeScript/Mongoose):**\n\n1. **Accounts module:**\n   - Clean controller/service separation\n   - DRY issue: duplicate email/username uniqueness checks\n   - Good error handling with ApiError\n   - Pagination properly implemented\n   - Uses aggregation for complex queries\n\n2. **Employees module:**\n   - Good permission-based filtering\n   - DRY issue: duplicate email/phone/code uniqueness checks in createEmployee and updateEmployee (3 identical checks)\n   - Proper RBAC with role-based access control\n   - The updateEmployee function has a lot of repeated checks\n\n3. **Attendances module:**\n   - MASSIVE CODE DUPLICATION: createAttendanceFromDevice, createAttendanceMobileByGPS, createAttendanceMobileByWifi, createAttendanceFE all share nearly identical attendance creation/update logic\n   - This is a clear DRY violation - the core attendance check-in logic should be extracted into a helper function\n   - Good GPS and WiFi validation\n   - Uses encrypted data for FE attendance\n\n4. **Checkins module:**\n   - Good separation between Schedule and Abnormal checkin\n   - validateCreatorInParticipants is a private method\n   - Good validation of time constraints\n   - Overall clean architecture\n\n5. **OKRs module:**\n   - Extremely complex aggregation pipeline in getOKRByFilter - lots of nested logic\n   - No DRY violations detected\n   - Good RBAC\n\n6. **Leave Requests module:**\n   - 656 lines in leaveRequests.service.ts - VERY LARGE\n   - Two-level approval workflow (Manager + HR)\n   - Good leave balance management\n   - Good notification system\n   - Some DRY issues: repeated employee lookup, approval logic patterns\n\n7. **Auth module:**\n   - Good token management (access + refresh)\n   - Cookie-based refresh token\n   - Solid implementation overall\n\n8. **Roles/Permissions module:**\n   - Proper use of transactions for consistency\n   - Redis caching for permissions with cache-busting on updates\n   - Service instantiates itself with PermissionService.callingPermissionMaps preventing race conditions\n\n9. **Niko modules:**\n   - Emotion: Good service\n\n, well-structured\n   - Orders: Uses transactions properly for complex operations\n   - Wallets: Good balance tracking\n   - Criteria: Has try-catch with generic error rethrow - not ideal\n   - Gifts: Good but has hardcoded 'PENDING' string (magic number)\n   - Cart: Clean service\n\n**FE (React/TypeScript/RTK Query):**\n\n1. **API files:**\n   - Good use of RTK Query with providesTags/invalidatesTags\n   - Some use of `any` types (attendanceApi, okrApi, leaveApi)\n   - Proper use of overrideExisting\n\n2. **AccountPage.tsx:**\n   - 413 lines - reasonable size\n   - Good separation of concerns with multiple forms\n   - Clean TypeScript usage\n   - No loading states, error handling, or prop drilling issues\n\n3. **EmployeePage.tsx:**\n   - 311 lines - reasonable size\n   - Clean patterns with hooks like usePermission, AccessControl\n   - Good use of memoization\n\n4. **NikoPage.tsx:**\n   - 779 lines - VERY LARGE, should be split into sub-components\n   - Hardcoded emotion data in component (should be from API)\n   - EMOTION_MAP created in render body\n\nNow I'm identifying the critical issues. The attendance module has massive code duplication across multiple files, the leaveRequests service is oversized at 656 lines, and there are hardcoded magic strings scattered throughout. The NikoPage component at 779 lines needs refactoring into smaller pieces. Beyond that, I'm seeing `any` types leaking across the FE API files, missing JSDoc comments in most places, and inconsistent error handling with empty catch blocks in some niko services. There's also mixed language usage between Vietnamese and English that should be standardized, and some files have unnecessary complexity that could be simplified."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have enough data to write the comprehensive code quality report. Let me create it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4mi0q9it66m6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":5824,"output":924,"totalTokens":101731,"cacheRead":89378,"cacheWrite":5605,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775982347614,"responseId":"062a8a0d36758ec7975bb77b6a44b7d6","__openclaw":{"id":"3f484677","seq":136}}]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776171303102}}
